	<section class=3D"container mt-6 mb-24 px-0 xs:px-4">
		<article class=3D"bg-white shadow-md p-8">
			<h2 class=3D"text-2xl font-light mb-6 border-b border-gray-200">What doe=
s this calculate?</h2>

			<div class=3D"flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-6">
				<figure class=3D"md:order-1 text-center text-xs text-gray-500 max-w-75 =
shrink-0">
					<img src=3D"https://pokemon.gameinfo.io/images/iv-help/eevee-range.png=
" alt=3D"Range of IVs for Eevee" class=3D"border border-gray-300 p-px">
					<figcaption class=3D"mt-2">Does this Eevee have good stats or not?!</f=
igcaption>
				</figure>

				<div>
					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600">This calculator simply attempts to =
calculate the IVs (<a href=3D"https://pokemon.gameinfo.io/en/tools/iv-calcu=
lator#what-are-ivs" class=3D"text-link hover:underline">what are Pok=C3=A9m=
on IVs?</a>) for your Pok=C3=A9mon based on the information available.</p>
					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">As multiple IVs can give the s=
ame CP and HP values for a Pok=C3=A9mon, sometimes the range given can be q=
uite large.</p>
					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
						For example, the Eevee pictured to the right, this could either be a =
great Pok=C3=A9mon with almost full IVs, or it could be a fairly useless
						29% Eevee.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</article>

		<article class=3D"bg-white shadow-md p-8 mt-8">
			<h2 class=3D"text-2xl font-light mb-6 border-b border-gray-200">How do I=
 use this tool?</h2>

			<div class=3D"flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center md:items-start gap-=
6">
				<figure class=3D"md:order-1 text-center text-xs text-gray-500 max-w-75 =
shrink-0">
					<img src=3D"https://pokemon.gameinfo.io/images/iv-help/stat-info.jpg" =
alt=3D"Inputs for IV calculator" class=3D"border border-gray-300 p-px">
				</figure>

				<div>
					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600">
						<strong>Step 1:</strong> Choose your Pok=C3=A9mon that you want to us=
e in the calculator.
					</p>

					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
						<strong>Step 2:</strong> Fill in the following values as shown on the=
 image:
						</p><div class=3D"mt-4 text-xs ml-2">
							<span class=3D"p-1.5 bg-red-700 font-bold text-white mr-1">A</span>
							CP
						</div>
						<div class=3D"mt-3 text-xs ml-2">
							<span class=3D"p-1.5 bg-red-700 font-bold text-white mr-1">B</span>
							HP
						</div>
						<div class=3D"mt-3 text-xs ml-2">
							<span class=3D"p-1.5 bg-red-700 font-bold text-white mr-1">C</span>
							Dust required to Power Up the Pok=C3=A9mon
						</div>
					<p></p>

					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
						<strong>Step 3:</strong> If you have just caught this Pok=C3=A9mon, a=
nd not powered it up, then check the 'just caught'
						box as it will help narrow down the results.
					</p>

					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
						<strong>Step 4:</strong> Click 'Calculate'.  The calculator will run =
and give you the possible IV combinations for your Pok=C3=A9mon below.
						If the range of possible combinations is too large, you can further r=
efine with the Appraisal system.
					</p>

					<h2 class=3D"text-2xl font-light mb-6 border-b border-gray-200 mt-8">W=
hat is the 'Appraisal' section?</h2>

					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">The appraisal system is a feat=
ure on Pok=C3=A9mon Go that gives you information on your Pok=C3=A9mon, hel=
ping you to know how good your Pok=C3=A9mon is.</p>
					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
						This calculator works seamlessly with the in-game appraisal system, l=
etting you directly enter the information that you get from the game.
						This will usually help you significantly narrow down your results.
					</p>

					<h2 class=3D"text-2xl font-light mb-6 border-b border-gray-200 mt-8">W=
hat's in the 'Advanced' section?</h2>

					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
						If you're still getting a range of results and want to know what your=
 exact IVs are, you can use this feature.
						This is a further way in which you can narrow down the results, but a=
t the cost of powering up your Pok=C3=A9mon.
					</p>

					<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
						To use this feature, enter the stats as normal, but then power up you=
r Pok=C3=A9mon one time, and enter the new stats in this advanced section.
						This tool will then re-calculate based on your new data, and will hel=
p to further narrow down your results.  You can do this several times if
						you are still getting multiple results.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</article>

		<article class=3D"bg-white shadow-md p-8 mt-8">
			<h2 id=3D"what-are-ivs" class=3D"text-2xl font-light mb-6 border-b borde=
r-gray-200">What is an IV in Pokemon Go?</h2>

			<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">Each Pokemon has 3 separate IVs:=
 these are hidden values between 0 and 15 for the Attack, Defense, and Stam=
ina stats. These values determine how powerful a Pokemon will be at its max=
imum level.</p>
			<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">
				Not all Pok=C3=A9mon are equal:  two max-level Pok=C3=A9mon can have di=
fferent IVs, resulting in one which will be more powerful then the others. =
For example, a level 40 <a href=3D"https://pokemon.gameinfo.io/en/pokemon/1=
31-lapras">Lapras</a> can have a CP of between 2,229 and 2,603.			</p>
			<p class=3D"text-sm text-gray-600 mt-4">This means that in the worst cas=
e, you could end up with a Lapras which is only 85% as powerful as it could=
 be!</p>
		</article>
	</section>
</div>

